SIMPLE: incrustation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incrustation
<hw>In`crus*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>incrustatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>incrustation</ets>. See
<er>Incrust</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of incrusting, or the state of being
incrusted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A crust or hard coating of anything upon or within a
body, as a deposit of lime, sediment, etc., from water on the inner
surface of a steam boiler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A covering or inlaying of marble,
mosaic, etc., attached to the masonry by cramp irons or
cement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Fine Arts)</fld> <def>Anything inlaid or
imbedded.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incrustment</ent>⟦br⟧
